#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an10.96"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an10.96:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 10 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 10 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.96:0.2"
msgid "10. Upālivagga "
msgstr "10. With Upāli "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 96. Kokanudasutta → kokanadasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an10.96:0.3"
msgid "96. Kokanudasutta "
msgstr "96. With Kokanada "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.196, sc1
msgctxt "an10.96:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ānando rājagahe viharati tapodārāme. "
msgstr "At one time Venerable Ānanda was staying near Rājagaha in the Hot Springs Monastery. "

msgctxt "an10.96:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ paccuṭṭhāya yena tapodā tenupasaṅkami gattāni parisiñcituṃ. "
msgstr "Then Ānanda rose at the crack of dawn and went to the hot springs to bathe. "

#. VAR: Tapodāya → tapode (bj, mr)
msgctxt "an10.96:1.3"
msgid "Tapodāya gattāni parisiñcitvā paccuttaritvā ekacīvaro aṭṭhāsi gattāni pubbāpayamāno. "
msgstr "When he had bathed and emerged from the water he stood in one robe drying himself. "

msgctxt "an10.96:1.4"
msgid "Kokanudopi kho paribbājako rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ paccuṭṭhāya yena tapodā tenupasaṅkami gattāni parisiñcituṃ. "
msgstr "The wanderer Kokanada also rose at the crack of dawn and went to the hot springs to bathe. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
#. VAR: kokanudo → kokanado (bj)
msgctxt "an10.96:2.1"
msgid "Addasā kho kokanudo paribbājako āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ. "
msgstr "He saw Ānanda coming off in the distance "

msgctxt "an10.96:2.2"
msgid "Disvāna āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "and said to him, "

#. VAR: kvettha → ko’ttha (bj) | ko tettha (si) | kvattha (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an10.96:2.3"
msgid "“kvettha, āvuso”ti? "
msgstr "“Who’s here, reverend?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.96:2.4"
msgid "“Ahamāvuso, bhikkhū”ti. "
msgstr "“I’m a mendicant, reverend.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an10.96:3.1"
msgid "“Katamesaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhūnan”ti? "
msgstr "“Of which mendicants?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.96:3.2"
msgid "“Samaṇānaṃ, āvuso, sakyaputtiyānan”ti. "
msgstr "“Of the ascetics who follow the Sakyan.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an10.96:4.1"
msgid "“Puccheyyāma mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ kiñcideva desaṃ, sace āyasmā okāsaṃ karoti pañhassa veyyākaraṇāyā”ti. "
msgstr "“I’d like to ask the venerable about a certain point, if you’d take the time to answer.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.96:4.2"
msgid "“Pucchāvuso, sutvā vedissāmā”ti. "
msgstr "“Ask, reverend. When I’ve heard it I’ll know.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
#. VAR: evaṃdiṭṭhi → evaṃdiṭṭhiko (s1-3)
msgctxt "an10.96:5.1"
msgid "“Kiṃ nu kho, bho, ‘sassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti—evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavan”ti? "
msgstr "“Is this your view: ‘The world is eternal. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.96:5.2"
msgid "“Na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, evaṃdiṭṭhi: "
msgstr "“That’s not my view, reverend.” "

msgctxt "an10.96:5.3"
msgid "‘sassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an10.96:6.1"
msgid "“Kiṃ pana, bho, ‘asassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti—evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavan”ti? "
msgstr "“Then is this your view: ‘The world is not eternal. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.96:6.2"
msgid "“Na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, evaṃdiṭṭhi: "
msgstr "“That’s not my view, reverend.” "

msgctxt "an10.96:6.3"
msgid "‘asassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.197, sc7
msgctxt "an10.96:7.1"
msgid "“Kiṃ nu kho, bho, antavā loko … pe … "
msgstr "“Then is this your view: ‘The world is finite …’ … "

msgctxt "an10.96:7.2"
msgid "anantavā loko … "
msgstr "‘The world is infinite …’ … "

msgctxt "an10.96:7.3"
msgid "taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīraṃ … "
msgstr "‘The soul and the body are the same thing …’ … "

msgctxt "an10.96:7.4"
msgid "aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīraṃ … "
msgstr "‘The soul and the body are different things …’ … "

msgctxt "an10.96:7.5"
msgid "hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā … "
msgstr "‘A Realized One exists after death …’ … "

msgctxt "an10.96:7.6"
msgid "na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā … "
msgstr "‘A Realized One doesn’t exist after death …’ … "

msgctxt "an10.96:7.7"
msgid "hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā … "
msgstr "‘A Realized One both exists and doesn’t exist after death …’ … "

msgctxt "an10.96:7.8"
msgid "neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti—evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavan”ti? "
msgstr "‘A Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist after death. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.96:7.9"
msgid "“Na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, evaṃdiṭṭhi: "
msgstr "“That’s not my view, reverend.” "

msgctxt "an10.96:7.10"
msgid "‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an10.96:8.1"
msgid "“Tena hi bhavaṃ na jānāti, na passatī”ti? "
msgstr "“Then, sir, do you neither know nor see?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.96:8.2"
msgid "“Na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, na jānāmi na passāmi. "
msgstr "“That’s not so, reverend. "

msgctxt "an10.96:8.3"
msgid "Jānāmahaṃ, āvuso, passāmī”ti. "
msgstr "I do know and see.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an10.96:9.1"
msgid "“‘Kiṃ nu kho, bho, sassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti—"
msgstr "“When asked about all these points, you say that’s not your view. "

msgctxt "an10.96:9.2"
msgid "evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavan’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an10.96:9.3"
msgid "‘na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, evaṃdiṭṭhi—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an10.96:9.4"
msgid "sassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti vadesi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "an10.96:10.1"
msgid "‘Kiṃ pana, bho, asassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an10.96:10.2"
msgid "evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavan’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an10.96:10.3"
msgid "‘na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, evaṃdiṭṭhi—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an10.96:10.4"
msgid "asassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti vadesi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "an10.96:11.1"
msgid "Kiṃ nu kho, bho, antavā loko … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an10.96:11.2"
msgid "anantavā loko … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an10.96:11.3"
msgid "taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīraṃ … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an10.96:11.4"
msgid "aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīraṃ … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an10.96:11.5"
msgid "hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an10.96:11.6"
msgid "na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an10.96:11.7"
msgid "hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an10.96:11.8"
msgid "neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an10.96:11.9"
msgid "evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavanti, iti puṭṭho samāno: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an10.96:11.10"
msgid "‘na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, evaṃdiṭṭhi—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an10.96:11.11"
msgid "neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti vadesi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "an10.96:12.1"
msgid "‘Tena hi bhavaṃ na jānāti na passatī’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno: "
msgstr "Yet when asked whether you neither know nor see, "

msgctxt "an10.96:12.2"
msgid "‘na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, na jānāmi na passāmi. "
msgstr "you say, ‘That’s not so, reverend. "

msgctxt "an10.96:12.3"
msgid "Jānāmahaṃ, āvuso, passāmī’ti vadesi. "
msgstr "I do know and see.’ "

msgctxt "an10.96:12.4"
msgid "Yathā kathaṃ panāvuso, imassa bhāsitassa attho daṭṭhabbo”ti? "
msgstr "How then should we see the meaning of this statement?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.198, sc13
msgctxt "an10.96:13.1"
msgid "“‘Sassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti kho, āvuso, diṭṭhigatametaṃ. "
msgstr "“‘The world is eternal. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly:’ that’s a misconception. "

msgctxt "an10.96:13.2"
msgid "‘Asassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti kho, āvuso, diṭṭhigatametaṃ. "
msgstr "‘The world is not eternal. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly:’ that’s a misconception. "

msgctxt "an10.96:13.3"
msgid "Antavā loko … pe … "
msgstr "‘The world is finite …’ … "

msgctxt "an10.96:13.4"
msgid "anantavā loko … "
msgstr "‘The world is infinite …’ … "

msgctxt "an10.96:13.5"
msgid "taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīraṃ … "
msgstr "‘The soul and the body are the same thing …’ … "

msgctxt "an10.96:13.6"
msgid "aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīraṃ … "
msgstr "‘The soul and the body are different things …’ … "

msgctxt "an10.96:13.7"
msgid "hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā … "
msgstr "‘A Realized One exists after death …’ … "

msgctxt "an10.96:13.8"
msgid "na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā … "
msgstr "‘A Realized One doesn’t exist after death …’ … "

msgctxt "an10.96:13.9"
msgid "hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā … "
msgstr "‘A Realized One both exists and doesn’t exist after death …’ … "

msgctxt "an10.96:13.10"
msgid "‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti kho, āvuso, diṭṭhigatametaṃ. "
msgstr "‘A Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist after death. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly:’ that’s a misconception. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
#. VAR: diṭṭhi → diṭṭhigatā (sabbattha)
#. VAR: yāvatā diṭṭhiṭṭhānaṃ diṭṭhiadhiṭṭhānaṃ diṭṭhipariyuṭṭhānaṃ diṭṭhisamuṭṭhānaṃ diṭṭhisamugghāto → yāvatā diṭṭhiṭṭhānā adhiṭṭhānaṃ pariyuṭṭhānaṃ samugghāto (s1-3) | yāvatā diṭṭhiṭṭhāna adhiṭṭhāna pariyuṭṭhāna samuṭṭhāna samugghāto (pts1)
msgctxt "an10.96:14.1"
msgid "Yāvatā, āvuso, diṭṭhi yāvatā diṭṭhiṭṭhānaṃ diṭṭhiadhiṭṭhānaṃ diṭṭhipariyuṭṭhānaṃ diṭṭhisamuṭṭhānaṃ diṭṭhisamugghāto, tamahaṃ jānāmi tamahaṃ passāmi. "
msgstr "I know and see the scope of convictions, the scope of grounds for views, fixation on views, obsession with views, the origin of views, and the uprooting of views. "

msgctxt "an10.96:14.2"
msgid "Tamahaṃ jānanto tamahaṃ passanto kyāhaṃ vakkhāmi: "
msgstr "Knowing and seeing thus, why should I say: "

msgctxt "an10.96:14.3"
msgid "‘na jānāmi na passāmī’ti? "
msgstr "‘I neither know nor see?’ "

msgctxt "an10.96:14.4"
msgid "Jānāmahaṃ, āvuso, passāmī”ti. "
msgstr "I do know and see.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "an10.96:15.1"
msgid "“Ko nāmo āyasmā, kathañca panāyasmantaṃ sabrahmacārī jānantī”ti? "
msgstr "“What is the venerable’s name? And how are you known among your spiritual companions?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.96:15.2"
msgid "“‘Ānando’ti kho me, āvuso, nāmaṃ. "
msgstr "“Reverend, my name is Ānanda. "

msgctxt "an10.96:15.3"
msgid "‘Ānando’ti ca pana maṃ sabrahmacārī jānantī”ti. "
msgstr "And that’s how I’m known among my spiritual companions.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.96:15.4"
msgid "“Mahācariyena vata kira, bho, saddhiṃ mantayamānā na jānimha: "
msgstr "“Goodness! I had no idea I was consulting such a great teacher as "

msgctxt "an10.96:15.5"
msgid "‘āyasmā ānando’ti. "
msgstr "Venerable Ānanda! "

msgctxt "an10.96:15.6"
msgid "Sace hi mayaṃ jāneyyāma: "
msgstr "If I had known who "

msgctxt "an10.96:15.7"
msgid "‘ayaṃ āyasmā ānando’ti, ettakampi no nappaṭibhāyeyya. "
msgstr "you were, I wouldn’t have said so much. "

msgctxt "an10.96:15.8"
msgid "Khamatu ca me āyasmā ānando”ti. "
msgstr "May Venerable Ānanda please forgive me.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an10.96:15.9"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ. "
msgstr ""

